The paper discusses the design and implementation of a digital hardware data structure for event management in spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and their applications (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of field-programmable gate arrays (FPGAs) for implementation, which is a topic covered under computer architecture (cs.AR). The structured heap queue is a data structure, which is a topic covered under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed solution, which is a topic covered under performance evaluation and benchmarking (cs.ET) and event management (cs.EM).
